        <stimulus>[Political cartoon showing a figure labeled "Direct Primary" breaking chains labeled "Boss Rule" while voters cheer]</stimulus>
        <prompt>The reform depicted in this cartoon was designed to:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Reduce party boss influence</option>
            <option letter="b">Increase voter turnout</option>
            <option letter="c">Limit campaign spending</option>
            <option letter="d">Expand suffrage rights</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The direct primary was designed to reduce the influence of party bosses by allowing voters, rather than party leaders, to select candidates for office.</explanation>
